# Environment Configuration for OctoFit Tracker Frontend

# This file documents the environment variables needed to run the OctoFit Tracker frontend.

# Setup

# Create a ".env.local" file in the "octofit-tracker/frontend" directory with the following content:

# GitHub Codespace name - required for Codespaces deployment
# If running locally, you can omit this or set it to an empty string
VITE_CODESPACE_NAME=your-codespace-name

# The API base URL is automatically constructed as:
# - Codespaces: https://{VITE_CODESPACE_NAME}-8000.app.github.dev/api
# - Local: http://localhost:8000/api

# How it works

# - In Codespaces: set VITE_CODESPACE_NAME to your Codespace's name (available in $CODESPACE_NAME)
# - Locally: leave VITE_CODESPACE_NAME empty or unset; the app will use localhost:8000

# The frontend automatically detects and constructs the correct API base URL in src/apiService.js.



### Example for Codespaces

```bash
VITE_CODESPACE_NAME=laughing-winner-4wxxwr4qr6r3qgrv
```

The API will then be available at:
```
https://laughing-winner-4wxxwr4qr6r3qgrv-8000.app.github.dev/api
```

### Example for Local Development

Leave the file empty or create it without the `VITE_CODESPACE_NAME` variable:

```bash
# .env.local (empty or not needed)
```

The API will then be available at:
```
http://localhost:8000/api
```
